---
title: "FIG. 2 — Phase State Machine from Version Control"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> 200: Feature requested

    200: 200 — No Branch\n(Feature not started)

    200 --> 210: Branch spec/feature-product created

    210: 210 — Product Spec In Progress\n(Branch exists, file not on main)

    210 --> 220: PR merged to main

    220: 220 — Product Spec Approved\n(File exists on main)

    220 --> 230: Branch spec/feature-design created

    230: 230 — Design Spec In Progress\n(Branch exists, file not on main)

    230 --> 240: PR merged to main

    240: 240 — Design Spec Approved\n(File exists on main)

    240 --> 250: Branch spec/feature-engineering created

    250: 250 — Engineering Spec In Progress\n(Branch exists, file not on main)

    250 --> 260: PR merged to main

    260: 260 — Engineering Spec Approved\n(File exists on main)

    260 --> 270: Implementation branch created

    270: 270 — Build Phase\n(Code implementation)

    270 --> 280: PR merged, deployed

    280: 280 — Deployed\n(Feature live)

    280 --> [*]

    note right of 210
        Phase detection reads ONLY:\n- Branch existence\n- File existence on branch vs main\nNo separate database queried
    end note
